Gently charred courgette, salty Greek style cheese and a thick tomato-y beef stew sit atop a
bed of fluffy couscous in this warm and hearty Middle Eastern inspired dish.

Place a #large pan{} over high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

When the oil is hot, add the @Irish beef mince{250%grams}.

Break up the beef with a #wooden spoon{} as it browns and cook for ~{5-6%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Trim the @courgette{1%unit} then slice into 1cm thick rounds.

Roughly chop the @chives{5%grams}(roughly chopped) (use scissors if easier).

Once the beef has browned, add the @ground cumin{1%sachet} and @paprika{1%sachet}. Stir and cook for ~{1%min}.

Pour in the @chopped tomato with onion & garlic{1%pack}, @honey{1%sachet} and @water{150%ml}.

> Double water amount for 4p.

Bring to the boil then reduce the heat to medium-low.

Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Leave the stew to simmer until thickened, ~{15-20%mins}.

Meanwhile, boil your #kettle{} (or a #pot{} of water if you haven't got one).

Add the @couscous{100%grams} and @beef stock{1%sachet} to a #medium bowl{}. Add a drizzle of @oil{to taste} and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Pour @water{200%ml}(boiling) into the bowl.

> Double water amount for 4p.

Stir together, cover and leave to the side for ~{10%mins} or until ready to serve.

Place another pan over high heat (no oil).

Add the courgette and leave to cook until charred, ~{4-5%mins} each side.

Transfer to a #bowl{}, sprinkle with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} and set aside.

Try the stew and season to taste with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and @?sugar{to taste} if needed.

Fluff up the couscous with a #fork{} and divide between bowls.

Spoon over the beef stew and top with charred courgette.

Crumble the @Greek style cheese{100%grams}(crumbled) over the stew and garnish with the chives.